Variable: A named location used to store data in memory.
Function: A block of reusable code that performs a specific task.
Loop: A way to repeat a block of code multiple times.
List: A collection of ordered, changeable items.
Tuple: A collection of ordered, unchangeable items.
Dictionary: A collection of key-value pairs.
Boolean: A data type with only two values: True or False.
String: A sequence of characters.
Integer: A whole number without a decimal point.
Float: A number with a decimal point.
